Public Sans Thin Regular (PublicSans-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'PublicSans-Thin', Everything looks good.

Pass

Public Sans Thin Regular (PublicSans-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Public Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Public Sans Thin'.

Pass

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'PublicSans-ExtraLight', Everything looks good.

Pass

'space' in NID 6 cause issues in fontbook for Mac.

NID 6 is 'PublicSans-ExtraLight', Everything looks good.

Public Sans ExtraLight Regular (PublicSans-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Public Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight' = NID 1 'Public Sans ExtraLight'.

Pass

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

NID 6 is 'PublicSans-Medium', Everything looks good.

Public Sans Medium Regular (PublicSans-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Public Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Public Sans Medium'.

Public Sans SemiBold Regular (PublicSans-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'PublicSans-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

Pass

'space' in NID 6 cause issues in fontbook for Mac.

NID 6 is 'PublicSans-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Public Sans SemiBold Regular (PublicSans-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Public Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Public Sans SemiBold'.

Pass

Public Sans ExtraBold Regular (PublicSans-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'PublicSans-ExtraBold', Everything looks good.

Public Sans ExtraBold Regular (PublicSans-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Public Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Public Sans ExtraBold'.

Public Sans Black Regular (PublicSans-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'PublicSans-Black', Everything looks good.

Pass

Public Sans Black Regular (PublicSans-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Public Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Public Sans Black'.
